org.itemscript.core.gwt
Class GwtCookieConnector

java.lang.Object
  org.itemscript.core.gwt.GwtCookieConnector
All Implemented Interfaces:
Connector, SyncGetConnector, SyncPutConnector, HasSystem
public class GwtCookieConnector
extends java.lang.Object
implements SyncGetConnector, SyncPutConnector, HasSystem

A connector class that allows you to store values in browser cookies.

This is associated with the "cookie:" scheme in GWT. The remainder of the URL after the colon and before any fragment identifier is used as the name of the cookie. Cookies are set as persistent with a 10 year lifetime and no path.

Note: This is experimental and might change or go away if it proves not to be useful. There are some potential problems with multiple browser windows attempting to access the same cookie that have not been addressed.

Author:
Jacob Davies
jacob@itemscript.org
